				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Odd isnt it...<BR>
<BR>
When some very nice piece of armor becomes a bit difficult to obtain and harder even to farm. As soon as it is clear how difficult it is, you have people saying its &quot;ridiculous&quot;. Well of course it is, you are trying to (and supposedly doing it) take down a Leader of a Faction that is high level. Didn't it ever cross your mind that it is possible that something like this would happen? It isn't Verant messing with you guys...<BR>
It isn't GMs messing with you guys.<BR>
It is a challenging aspect of the game that makes Velious so awesome. Everything deals with Quests, new challenges, flip flop faction hits, unknown allies and miscontrued enemies. It makes it for more exploring and detailed trials... in short, it is called Roleplay, not roll-play. Look at the changes they ahve made with grouping, look at the changes they ahve made with characters' races and class adjustments...<BR>
<BR>
It isn't something made and designed by the players, but by the Team at Verant, hence, the classes are going to be extremely different. Like saying &quot;why can't monks get this...&quot;<BR>
or &quot;why doesnt my druid...&quot; and so on and so forth, and then backed by Culture, T.V shows, books, writings, historic fact...<BR>
Because it isn't designed off of them. That is why. All in all, it is just a thing to be done, just to do it, live it, experience it, and deal with it. It happens, just like levelling.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Aanladar D`Lemming<BR>
KneelingMonk of the 39th Trial to Enlightenment<BR>
